<h3><strong><span style="color: #000000;">Why Should I Become AÂ Member?</span></strong></h3>
<span style="color: #000000;">EAA benefits include:</span>
<ul>
	<li><span style="color: #000000;">Wage and benefits package in place through July 1, 2016.</span></li>
	<li><span style="color: #000000;">A dues rateÂ that isÂ the lowest of any City union. This is the identical rate you pay as a "Fair Share" payer.</span></li>
	<li><span style="color: #000000;">EAA's comprehensive dental, vision, chiropractic, and acupuncture plan is available for members only.</span></li>
	<li><span style="color: #000000;">Members have a voice in union affairs, ensured by the rights guaranteed in EAA's Constitution and By-Laws.</span></li>
	<li><span style="color: #000000;">Members can run for an elected office in the next election. No length of membership requirement.</span></li>
	<li><span style="color: #000000;">Members can learn to be an on-the-job representative for the Union to advocate for your co-workers. No length of membership requirement.</span></li>
	<li><span style="color: #000000;">Only members can vote on your next contract and other issues important to you in the workplace. There is no length of membership requirement to vote.</span></li>
	<li><span style="color: #000000;">Education in your rights and how your Union can ensure you are treated fairly in the workplace is available for members.</span></li>
	<li><span style="color: #000000;">So what are you waiting for? Take advantage of this opportunity now!</span></li>
</ul>
<h2><strong><span style="color: #000000;">IMPORTANT INFORMATION</span></strong></h2>
<span style="color: #000000;">This submittal will direct EAA to send you a dues authorization card, which must be signed and returned to the Union before your membership can be effective.</span>

<span style="color: #000000;">Your valid original signature on the dues card is the only authorization for membership that is recognized by the City of Los Angeles. The card must be the exact size, shape, and weight of paper for their files. The City will not accept electronic authorization.</span>

<span style="color: #000000;">EAA will submit your dues card to the City Controller's office.</span>

